race.description: Force By Emeco Ray Mcgee Memorial Mdn
race.comment: PRINCE OF BONDI (1) is busting to win and improved again last time in stronger grade. The gate is a touch awkward, but he'll push forward and is capable of going one better. SLIPPERY FISH (9) debuts and has switched to the top stable. Has been well trialled over a period and found a place the latest at Belmont. Has a low barrier and Fiore's booking suggests she's pleasing. The betting will be key. VAIN UNIVERSE (4) was better here last time and keeps the 3kg claim. He can get some of the money in this lineup. WHISKERS HARBOUR (3) resumes and has placed fresh. Faithful is a positive jockey booking and she owns a Lark Hill trial win.
